{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:14:13.397371+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I now have all the information needed. Here's the full picture:\n\n---\n\n## How the Template Switches Between Development and Production API Base Paths\n\nThe template uses **three environment files** (`dotenv` style) to set the `VUE_APP_BASE_API` variable, which acts as the API base path prefix for every request:\n\n| File | `VUE_APP_BASE_API` | Typical Use |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.env.development` | `/dev-api` | Local dev server (`npm run dev`) |\n| `.env.staging` | `/stage-api` | Pre-production / staging environment |\n| `.env.production` | `/prod-api` | Production builds (`npm run build`) |\n\n**How it works mechanically:**\n\n1. **Vue CLI** automatically loads the `.env.*` file that matches the current `NODE_ENV` and exposes `VUE_APP_*` variables to the client-side code at build time.\n2. The API service layer (in `src`) reads `process.env.VUE_APP_BASE_API` to prefix every HTTP request.\n3. **In development**, `vue.config.js` activates the **mock server** via `devServer.before: require('./mock/mock-server.js')`. The mock server's `responseFake()` function constructs Express route matchers using `new RegExp(`${process.env.VUE_APP_BASE_API}${url}`)`, so the mock routes respond to paths like `/dev-api/vue-admin-template/user/login`.\n4. **In production/staging**, there is no mock server—requests with the `/prod-api` or `/stage-api` prefix are expected to hit a real backend (typically behind a reverse proxy that strips the prefix).\n\nAdditionally, `vue.config.js` sets `publicPath` to `'/'` in development but `'/vue3-admin-template/'` in production, controlling where static assets are served from.\n\n---\n\n## Mock Login Usernames and Their Tokens\n\nThe mock user credentials are defined in **`mock/user.js`**:\n\n| Username | Token Received |\n|---|---|\n| `admin` | `admin-token` |\n| `editor` | `editor-token` |\n\n**How login works in the mock:**\n\n1. A `POST` to `/vue-admin-template/user/login` sends `{ username, password }`.\n2. The handler looks up `username` in the `tokens` map and returns the matching token (e.g., `{ code: 20000, data: { token: 'admin-token' } }`).\n3. On subsequent `GET` requests to `/vue-admin-template/user/info`, the token is passed as a query parameter. The `users` map resolves it to a user profile:\n\n| Token | Roles | Display Name | Introduction |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `admin-token` | `['admin']` | Super Admin | \"I am a super administrator\" |\n| `editor-token` | `['editor']` | Normal Editor | \"I am an editor\" |\n\nAny other username returns an error: *\"Account and password are incorrect.\"*", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 662, "prompt_tokens": 8312, "total_tokens": 8974, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 29, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8128, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0006852408, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001093008, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00057594}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863241-SGhajnTEWSWjzx7TQBhk", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3b8-8ac2-7b22-8546-cf8b6e36abf8-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8312, "output_tokens": 662, "total_tokens": 8974, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8128}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 29}}}}]}}}
